winter desserts have a heartier personality than the delicate peach tarts berries and cream combinations or refreshing melon soups of summer these fruits are out of season nonetheless plenty of rich winter sweets can be fruit based here are three of them one is a custardy bread pudding sweetened with maple syrup studded with bits of banana and best served warm another is a pear cake infused with amaretto and strewn with toasty almonds and the third is a sturdy raisin cake flavored with port wine excellent to serve in slices with a glass of port and even a wedge of mild pecorino cheese for the raisin cake it is important to use an amber colored tawny port not a ruby sweet port banana bread pudding with maple syrup total time 1 1 2 hours plus cooling 1 1 2 tablespoons unsalted butter 3 1 2 cups 1 inch cubes stale or lightly toasted brioche or hallah 1 2 3 cups milk 1 3 cup maple syrup pinch nutmeg 2 eggs lightly beaten 1 1 2 cups diced banana about 2 bananas not too ripe 1 tablespoon brown sugar 3 4 cup heavy cream whipped 1 preheat oven to 350 degrees butter a six cup round baking dish with half a tablespoon butter 2 put bread pieces in mixing bowl heat milk and syrup in saucepan until syrup dissolves into milk add nutmeg pour over bread and allow to sit about 30 minutes to saturate stir in eggs fold in diced banana 3 transfer mixture to baking dish sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with remaining butter bake 35 to 40 minutes until starting to look crusty on top serve warm with whipped cream yield 6 servings winter pear cake total time 1 hour plus cooling 1 2 cup unsalted butter 1 stick at room temperature 5 medium size ripe pears peeled cored and cut in eighths juice of 1 2 lemon 1 2 cup amaretto liqueur 1 cup flour 1 teaspoon baking powder pinch of salt 3 4 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar 2 eggs 1 2 teaspoon almond extract 3 tablespoons sliced almonds 1 preheat oven to 375 degrees use some of the butter to grease a nine inch round springform cake pan 2 toss pear slices in bowl with lemon and amaretto set aside whisk flour baking powder and salt in a bowl set aside 3 beat six tablespoons butter until light beat in three fourths of a cup of sugar until fluffy beat in eggs one at a time fold in flour mixture add almond extract and spread batter in pan drain pear slices reserving amaretto and arrange in a pattern over batter sprinkle with almonds dot with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar 4 bake about 45 minutes until golden brown remove from oven and drizzle reserved amaretto over top of cake cool remove from pan and serve yield 8 servings raisin cake with port total time 1 1 2 hours plus cooling 1 2 cup unsalted butter 1 stick at room temperature 1 1 2 cups cake flour 1 1 2 cups dark raisins 1 cup tawny port 1 2 teaspoon cinnamon 1 teaspoon baking powder 1 4 teaspoon baking soda 1 2 teaspoon salt 1 2 cup honey 2 large eggs 1 preheat oven to 350 degrees use half a tablespoon of butter to grease an eight  or nine inch springform pan dust with a little flour 2 put raisins in small bowl and mix with half a cup of port sift together remaining flour with cinnamon baking powder baking soda and salt 3 beat remaining butter until fluffy slowly beat in honey beat in eggs one at a time beat batter one minute stir in flour mixture in thirds alternating with remaining port fold in raisins and port spread mixture in pan and bake about 55 minutes until cake tester comes out clean yield 8 servings

